articles.description: Deion "Coach Prime" Sanders kicked off his second season at Colorado with a combative news conference Friday when he also celebrated his 57th birthday and became a grandfather.
articles.headline: Deion Sanders spars with media in testy Colorado presser

articles.description: Plaintiffs' attorneys in a federal antitrust lawsuit against the NCAA that is not part of a recent $2.78 billion settlement agreement filed a motion Friday asking a judge to deny preliminary approval of the deal.
articles.headline: Plaintiffs in Colorado lawsuit v. NCAA ask judge to deny settlement

images.name: NCAA logo [600x400] - Copy
images.caption: With college sports on the verge of sweeping change that could have long-term financial implications, two private investment firms have created Collegiate Athletic Solutions, which is trying to cash in on a  landscape that's facing significant upheaval.

articles.description: Former Florida State running back Rodney Hill blames a "bad agent" for his circuitous path through the transfer portal to Arkansas.

articles.description: Jim Harbaugh has accepted an invitation to be Michigan's honorary captain for the Wolverines' Aug. 31 game against Fresno State.

images.name: Harbaugh relays his continued hope for college athletics
images.caption: Jim Harbaugh speaks of his hope that, one day, the NCAA will be about what's best for its athletes.
